    "created_at": "2026-03-24T13:18:39Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-03-24T13:18:39Z",
    "body": "I've been looking into this issue. The root cause is in `is_module_disabled_in_config()` (context.rs) — when a module like `pijul_channel` has no section in the user's TOML config, `get_module_config()` returns `None`, so the disabled check defaults to `false` even though the module's config struct defaults to `disabled: true`.\n\nMy approach: add a `DEFAULT_DISABLED_MODULES` constant listing the 21 modules that default to `disabled: true`, and modify `is_module_disabled_in_config()` to fall back to this list when no explicit `disabled` field exists in user config. This preserves all existing behavior while skipping unnecessary module invocations.\n\nOpening a draft PR shortly.",
